        text: "PROFILE Rear Admiral Mustapha Bala Hassan is an accomplished Communication Specialist with a wealth of knowledge in national security and war studies. He has completed all relevant military courses at various prestigious institutions.  He has a Master of Science Degree in National Security and War Studies from the National Defence University Islamabad, Pakistan, 2015. A Master of Art Degree in International Relations from the University of Ghana, Accra, Ghana, 2007. During the course of his career Admiral Hassan has held several appointments some of which are; Commanding Officer, Nigerian Navy Ship NWAMBA Commandant Nigerian Navy Ship QUORRA Until his appointment as the Flag Officer Commanding Western Naval Command he was the Commandant Naval War College Nigeria, Calabar. Admiral Hassan has the following awards and decorations: Grand Service Star Fellow Defence College (+) Naval War College (+)  Passed Staff Course double dagger (+) (+)  The FOC is the initiator of the following Operations  1. Operation WATER GUARD 2. Operation SECURED LINE Admiral Hassan is the 2023 recipient of the prestigious CNS Command and Leadership Award. He is the force Commander Operation AWATSE South West, Nigeria. His hobbies include, mentoring, travelling, golfing and sailing. He is the 44th Flag Officer Commanding Western Naval Command, the premier Command. He superintends over many coastal states, Islands and hinterlands. "
